sequenceDiagram
    actor U as Usuario
    participant C as Cliente React
    participant G as API Gateway (Nginx)
    participant A as Auth Service
    participant P as PostgreSQL
    participant K as Keycloak
    participant KF as Kafka

    U->>C: 1. Completa formulario de registro
    C->>C: 2. Validar campos (email, password, nombre, edad)
    
    C->>G: 3. POST /users/register
    Note over C,G: {email, password, firstName, lastName, age, clientId, role}
    
    G->>A: 4. Proxy → /users/register
    
    A->>P: 5. SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = $1
    
    alt Email ya registrado
        P-->>A: Usuario existe
        A-->>C: 409 Conflict (email already exists)
        C-->>U: Mostrar error "Email ya registrado"
    else Email no existe
        P-->>A: Usuario no existe
        
        A->>P: 6. INSERT INTO users (email, first_name, last_name, age, client_id, role)
        P-->>A: userId (UUID)
        
        A->>K: 7. POST /admin/realms/{realm}/users
        Note over A,K: Crear usuario en Keycloak con atributos postgresId, age, clientId, role
        
        K-->>A: keycloakId
        
        A->>K: 8. POST /admin/realms/{realm}/users/{id}/role-mappings/clients/{clientUuid}
        Note over A,K: Asignar rol (estudiante/ama-de-casa/trabajador)
        
        K-->>A: Rol asignado
        
        A->>P: 9. UPDATE users SET keycloak_id = $1 WHERE id = $2
        
        A->>KF: 10. Produce evento "user_registered"
        Note over A,KF: topic: auth-events
        
        A-->>C: 11. 201 Created (userId, keycloakId, email, role)
        C-->>U: 12. Mostrar éxito y redirigir a login
    end